(firstQuint)A Study Comparing the Efficacy and Safety of IDP-121 and IDP-121 Vehicle Lotion in the Treatment of Acne Vulgaris.

 This is a multicenter, randomized, double-blind, parallel group, vehicle-controlled, 12-week study to evaluate relative changes in inflammatory and non-inflammatory lesion counts, as well as treatment success using an Evaluator's Global Severity Scale (EGSS) in subjects with moderate to severe acne.

 IDP-121 is a lotion for the topical treatment of acne.

